[3] French Antilles and Guiana
Date: 31 Mar-6 Apr 2014
Source: Institut de Veille Sanitaire (French Institute for Public Health Surveillance, InVS), Point Epidemiologique no. 13 [in French, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, summ., edited]
http://www.invs.sante.fr/content/download/86747/318547/version/60/file/pe_chikungunya_antilles_100414.pdf [in French, transl. Mod. TY]


Cases since the end of November, 2013:
- St Martin: (susp.) 2910 cases; (probable or confirmed) 791 cases; deaths 3. Stable, low level.
- St Barthelemy: (susp.) 444 cases; (probable or confirmed) 135 cases. Stable, low level.
- Martinique: (susp.) 13 500, (probable or confirmed) 1284 cases; deaths 2. Increasing slightly, all municipalities affected.
- Guadeloupe: (susp.) 3690 cases; (probable or confirmed) 942 cases; deaths 1. In epidemic status.
- French Guiana: (probable or confirmed) 27 cases; (imported) 15 cases. Moderate, Kourou and Matoury municipalities with active transmission.

